description:
On December the 21st, Eritrea's High Level Task Force on COVID-19 re-issued the following new Guideline:

Vital social occasions – funerals, mourning etc. -will be held with a small number of participants – not more than 10 people. Other social events will have to be postponed;

This will be effective from Tuesday morning (6:00 a.m.), December 22nd onwards. It will be assessed periodically in a comprehensive manner and relaxed depending on the trajectory and threat of the COVID-19 pandemic.
